## Short-term memory — `/scratch/`

Thread-scoped notes backed by graph state.  Files under `/scratch/` survive
sandbox container recycling within the current thread but are lost when the
thread ends.

Use for:
- Intermediate reasoning artifacts you want to re-read after an
  `execute_python` restart.
- Handing off context to a downstream sub-agent in the same thread.

Access via the standard filesystem tools: `read_file`, `edit_file`,
`write_file`, `ls`.  Files under `/scratch/` are not visible to other users
or future conversations.
